The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Friday, January 16, 2004 				 Naxalites behead mole
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Laljal (West Midnapore), Jan. 15: Jharkhand Party (Naren Hansda) worker Kamal Mahato was hacked to death and beheaded by alleged Maoist Communist Centre activists here last evening.																								A hunt is on for the group of 40 armed Naxalites that came to Laljal village in Belpahari, 250 km from Calcutta. 																								The police said the assailants were speaking in Hindi and charged Kamal with acting as a police informer. They left behind MCC posters that said Khoon ka badla khoon (Blood for blood). 																								The MCC activists have fled towards Bankura, said district superintendent of police Praveen Kumar, who is now camping at Belpahari. Jawans of the Border Security Force, who were posted here recently, have launched a combing operation along with the polices special combat force.																								Kamal was sitting near a bonfire with his wife, brother, three daughters, son and neighbours in front of his house when the Naxalites came. They dragged Kamal out of the huddle and pointed guns at us. When my husband tried to intervene, they broke his legs, said Hiranmoyi, the wife of Kamals elder brother.																								Kamals wife Namita said: They hacked him, pinned him to the floor and hit him on the neck with a heavy chopper.
